title: Leading Global Contributor to Development Aid
description: In 2017, Sweden provided 1.02% of its Gross National Income (GNI) as Official Development Assistance (ODA), marking it as one of the highest contributors globally.

title: High Tax Revenue from Other Sources
description: In 2022, 28.21% of Sweden's revenue came from other taxes, indicating a diversified tax base.

title: Minimal Particulate Emission Damage
description: Sweden's particulate emission damage was only 0.009% of its GNI in 2021, showcasing its commitment to environmental sustainability.

title: Strong Net Primary Income from Abroad
description: In 2023, Sweden's net primary income from abroad was valued at 176.7 billion LCU, reflecting a robust international economic presence.

title: Near-Universal Male Secondary School Enrollment
description: In 2015, Sweden achieved a 99.81% net enrollment rate for males in secondary education, highlighting its strong educational system.
